        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2j0p/8d56c310-3157-40b9-985f-771b9aa63e77/b57be2a0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2j0q.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2j0p/8d56c310-3157-40b9-985f-771b9aa63e77/b57be2a0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2j0q.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Option 2\">",
        "<img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2jvh/6918775d-08e8-4ffc-bc04-8f70c88d3ba5/b624ccd0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2jvi.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2jvh/6918775d-08e8-4ffc-bc04-8f70c88d3ba5/b624ccd0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2jvi.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Option 3\">",
        "<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2kog/06991155-7a27-4127-a3f7-a18db9c6d83b/b6c3f300-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2koh.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd2kog/06991155-7a27-4127-a3f7-a18db9c6d83b/b6c3f300-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd2koh.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Option 4\"></p>"
      ],
      "correctOption": 0,
      "solution": "<p>The propene on reaction with nitrosyl chloride, NOCl produces an adduct as shown below.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4cri/1fc23079-8042-4dc6-93d5-08d222335c4c/e844fbe0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4crj.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4cri/1fc23079-8042-4dc6-93d5-08d222335c4c/e844fbe0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4crj.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Explanation 1\"></p>\n<p>The propylene undergoes an electrophilic addition reaction, following the Markownikoff's rule.</p>\n<p>Step 1:</p>\n<p>Decomposition of nitrosyl chloride</p>\n<p>$$ \\mathrm{NOCl} \\rightleftharpoons \\mathrm{NO}^{+}+\\mathrm{Cl}^{-} $$</p>\n<p>Step 2:</p>\n<p>Addition of positive part of nitrosyl chloride on carbon atom of double bond containing highest number (2 degree carbocation) of hydrogen atoms. A stable intermediate is produced, during this slow step.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4dk0/644a9afe-2121-4004-ade9-265268f2b2e6/e8e18a00-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4dk1.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4dk0/644a9afe-2121-4004-ade9-265268f2b2e6/e8e18a00-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4dk1.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Explanation 2\">Step 3:</p>\n<p>Addition of chloride ion on carbon atom of double bond containing least number of hydrogen atoms. The adduct is obtained during a very fast reaction.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/fly/@width/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4e2y/f9ef20aa-e892-42db-b40d-bf0418f25c40/e949c1b0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4e2z.png?format=png\" data-orsrc=\"https://app-content.cdn.examgoal.net/image/jaoe38c1mgtd4e2y/f9ef20aa-e892-42db-b40d-bf0418f25c40/e949c1b0-aa86-11f0-a81b-79e201448ba7/file-jaoe38c1mgtd4e2z.png\" loading=\"lazy\" style=\"max-width:100%;height:auto;display:block;margin:0 auto;max-height:40vh;vertical-align:baseline\" alt=\"IIT-JEE 2006 Chemistry - Hydrocarbons Question 3 English Explanation 3\"></p>",
      "marks": 3,
      "negativeMarks": -1,
      "topic": "Hydrocarbon"
    },
